# Component Rules

## Always use shared components from `src/components/ui/core.tsx`

| Need | Use |
|------|-----|
| Container/panel | `Card`, `CardHeader`, `CardTitle`, `CardContent` |
| Actions | `Button` (variants: default, outline, ghost, secondary, danger) |
| Text input | `Input` |
| Dropdown / filter / pick value | `Select`, `SelectTrigger`, `SelectValue`, `SelectContent`, `SelectItem` |
| Status/tag | `Badge` (including tier-s/a/b/c variants) |
| Modal | `Dialog`, `DialogContent`, `DialogHeader`, `DialogTitle` |
| Divider | `Separator` |

## Do NOT

- Create new button/card/badge styles inline when a core component exists
- Hardcode background colors on cards (`bg-[#050505]`, `bg-[#0A0A0A]`, etc.)
- Add `italic` to any className
- Use `font-black` for headings — use `font-bold` or `font-semibold`
- Duplicate nav config — use `NAV_ITEMS` from `@/config/nav`

## Layout patterns

- **Public website**: `Layout` — full-width `Header` with horizontal nav (`HeaderNav` at xl+), mobile drawer (`Sidebar`), bottom `MobileNav` (xl:hidden). No left sidebar on desktop.
- **Admin**: `AdminLayout` — left `AdminSidebar` + `AdminHeader` + main (`max-w-[1600px]`)
- **PageContainer** (`src/components/layout/PageContainer.tsx`) — shared horizontal padding + max-width. Use instead of duplicating `max-w-[1400px] px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8`.
  - `full` — 1400px (home, lists, grids)
  - `article` — max-w-3xl (~768px) prose column
  - `reading` — max-w-4xl (~896px) editor / long-form
  - `narrow` — max-w-2xl
- Public shell: `Header`, `Layout` main, and `Footer` use `PageContainer`.
- **PageHeader** (`src/components/layout/PageHeader.tsx`) — page title + description + optional action slot (filters, CTAs).
- Admin content max-width: `max-w-[1600px]` in `AdminLayout` (Phase 7 may add `AdminPageContainer`).
- Main padding: `p-4 sm:p-6 lg:p-8` (public), `p-4 sm:p-6` (admin)

## Hero cost colors

Use `heroCostBarClass()` / `heroCostBadgeClass()` from `@/lib/cost-colors` instead of raw `purple-500`, `blue-500`, etc.

## Class merging

Always use `cn()` from `@/lib/utils` when combining conditional classes.
